us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameVector3DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple3DBasics, FixedFrameVector3DBasics, FrameChangeable, FrameTuple3DBasics, FrameTuple3DReadOnly, FrameVector3DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Tuple3DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple3D.interfaces.Vector3DReadOnly
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector3D

    public interface FrameVector3DBasics
extends FixedFrameVector3DBasics, FrameTuple3DBasics, FrameChangeable
    Write and read interface for a 3D vector expressed in a changeable reference frame, i.e. the reference frame in which this vector is expressed can be changed.

    In addition to representing a Vector3DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameVector3DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FrameVector3DBasics extends Vector3DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector3DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameVector3DBasics.
